               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>I brought a lighter up that morning, I made her fast on the outside; coming over the craft with my clothes on my arm, I slipped down; they called out, somebody was going to rob the lighter; they came and charged me; I said, do not make a noise, I will go with you.</p>
               <p>He called Mr. Lovell, a Custom-house officer, Mr. Benson, a smith, 
